SIMPLE: niggardly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Niggardly
<hw>Nig"gard*ly</hw> <pr>(n⟦icr⟧g"g⟦etil⟧rd*l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Meanly covetous or avaricious in dealing with others; stingy;
niggard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where the owner of the house will be bountiful, it is not for the
steward to be <qex>niggardly</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Avaricious; covetous; parsimonious; sparing;
miserly; penurious; sordid; stingy. See <er>Avaricious</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Niggardly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Niggardly
<hw>Nig"gard*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a niggard
manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Niggardness</ent>⟦br⟧
